Nigeria’s Chairman of the Senate Committee on Local and Foreign Debts, Senator Shehu Sani has again reacted to the tenure elongation of the All Progressive Congress (APC) National Working Commitee (NWC), led by John Oyegun, chairman of the party. Governors of the All Progressives Congress (APC) had dismissed media reports that there was disagreement between them and President Muhammadu Buhari over tenure elongation for the APC national and state executives. Sani a tweet said,"Baba Said no to tenure elongation,the Governors who said yes to tenure elongation are not called Anti Buhari. "Baba said no to reordering of sequence of election,the senators who said yes to reordering of election are called Anti Buhari." Baba Said no to tenure elongation,the Governors who said yes to tenure elongation are not called Anti Buhari. 
Baba said no to reordering of sequence of election,the senators who said yes to reordering of election are called Anti Buhari.
— Senator Shehu Sani (@ShehuSani) April 7, 2018